data.enText: a reddish-brown substance that is formed on some metals by the action of water and air
a plant disease that causes reddish-brown spots; the fungus that causes this disease
if metal rusts or sth rusts it, it becomes covered with rust
Water had got in and rusted the engine.
to be gradually destroyed by rust
to be gradually destroyed by rust

tr: any of various fungi causing rust disease in plants
the formation of reddish-brown ferric oxides on iron by low-temperature oxidation in the presence of water
a plant disease that produces a reddish-brown discoloration of leaves and stems
a red or brown oxide coating on iron or steel caused by the action of oxygen and moisture
become destroyed by water, air, or a corrosive such as an acid
cause to deteriorate due to the action of water, air, or an acid
example: The steady dripping of water rusted the metal stopper in the sink

tr: of the brown color of rust

value.def: Rust is a brown substance that forms on iron or steel, for example when it comes into contact with water.

example.ex: Manufacturers are looking into building cars out of plastic to avoid the problem of rust.
example.tran: 制造商们正研究如何用塑料制造车辆，以避免生锈。

value.def: When a metal object rusts, it becomes covered in rust and often loses its strength.

example.ex: Copper nails are better than iron nails because the iron rusts...
example.tran: 铜钉比铁钉好，因为铁会生锈。

example.ex: There was an old rusting bolt on the door.
example.tran: 门上有一个生锈的旧门闩。

value.def: Rust is sometimes used to describe things that are reddish-brown in colour.

example.ex: ...turquoise woodwork with accent colours of rust and ochre.
example.tran: 主色调为深褐色和赭色的青绿色木制品

value.def: Rust is a disease which affects plants. It is caused by a fungus.
